commitResults.messageTitle: Provide docs for the implementation of Sort Event
Enhance sort feature to auto-sort when events are changed
commitResults.messageBody:
Sorting requires user to enter a SortCommand.

This can be a hassle to the user, and may produced unexpected,
inconsistent results. Eg. user thinks that it had been sorted,
when in actual fact it isnt, thus possibly causing the user to
miss an event.

Let's automatically sort the list of events whenever an event is
added, edited or deleted, to produce a consistent ordering of the
list of events. This is done via a listener.

A listener is a clean way to check for list changes, and can cater
to any future commands that also modify the list.

Subsequently, the SortCommand shall be removed.

ShowNext command shows the next up coming events.
If a number is provided to the command, the next xx number
(as provided) of events will be shown.

ShowNext command uses the keyword "next".

Checkstyles checks are passed locally.

Testing is done only for parsing of the command.
No test cases for the handling of the command (need to consider how
to create the test case when the outcome is time-dependent).
